  <div class="container">

    <h1>Research & Development Projects</h1>

    <div class="project">
      <h2>Teaching Artificial Intelligence to Pre-Service Elementary Teachers</h2>
      <span class="tag">AI Education</span>
      <p>
        This project explores how elementary teacher candidates can meaningfully engage with AI concepts through hands-on activities, robotics, and classroom integration. It aims to prepare future teachers to embed AI literacy into core subject areas and foster equitable and age-appropriate AI understanding in K–6 settings.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
      <h2>STEM Strong</h2>
      <span class="tag">NSF DRK–12</span>
      <p>
        Funded by the National Science Foundation (DRK–12), STEM Strong provides professional development and curriculum support to rural educators implementing interdisciplinary STEM teaching strategies. The program focuses on self-efficacy, place-based learning, and contextualized science education.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
      <h2>My Home, My Health</h2>
      <span class="tag">NIH SEPA</span>
      <p>
        Supported by the NIH SEPA program, this initiative engages youth and families in health education through culturally relevant, community-based STEM learning. It emphasizes environmental health literacy and empowers students to explore health issues in their own homes and communities.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>

